      • getColor

        public abstract java.awt.Color getColor​(int eutype,
                                        double tf,
                                        double tg,
                                        double tsat,
                                        double voidfrac)
        Determine the color for a thermal-hydraulic state by intepolating over the appropriate range.
        Parameters:
        eutype - the engineering units type of the given value. This should be either Real.SI or Real.BRITISH.
        tf - the liquid phase fluid temperature.
        tg - the vapor phase fluid temperature.
        tsat - the saturation temperature.
        voidfrac - the void fraction of the fluid.
        Returns:
        the color for this fluid condition.

      • getColor

        public abstract java.awt.Color getColor​(int eutype,
                                        double value)
        Determine the color for a data value by intepolating over the range. If the data value exceeds the maximum value, return the maximum color, if it falls below the minimum, return the minimum color.
        Parameters:
        eutype - the engineering units type of the given value. This should be either Real.SI or Real.BRITISH.
        value - the data value.
        Returns:
        the Color for the given data value.

      • getGeneric2DChannelNames

        public java.lang.String[] getGeneric2DChannelNames​(java.lang.String codeID,
                                                   java.lang.String volumeID)
        Gets the two channel names returned from the getPatternChannel and getSecondParameterPatternChannel methods. The array will have two entries: the first index is the first parameter channel name, the second index is the second parameter channel name. The two channel names may be "-not set-" for an invalid channel name.
        Parameters:
        codeID - the animation module name
        volumeID - the volumeID to use
        Returns:
        the channel names
